==Starting off==
* '''Player:''' Now I am a knight of the round table, do you have any more quests for me?
* '''King Arthur:''' Aha! I'm glad you are here! I am sending out various knights on an important quest. I was wondering if you too would like to take up this quest?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Tell me of this quest.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me of this quest.
** '''King Arthur:''' Well, we recently found out that the Holy Grail has passed into Gielinor.
** '''King Arthur:''' This is most fortuitous!
** '''King Arthur:''' None of my knights ever did return with it last time. Now we have the opportunity to give it another go, maybe this time we will have more luck!
** {{tcond|If the player's combat level is less than 50:}}
*** {{tbox|Before starting this quest, be aware that your combat level is lower than the recommended level of 50.}}
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player's combat level is more than 50:}}
*** {{tselect|Start the Holy Grail quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'd enjoy trying that.
*** '''King Arthur:''' Go speak to Merlin. He may be able to give a better clue as to where it is now you have freed him from that crystal.
*** '''King Arthur:''' He has set up his workshop in the room next to the library.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' I may come back and try that later.
*** '''King Arthur:''' Be sure that you come speak to me soon then.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I am weary of questing for the time being...}}
* '''Player:''' I am weary of questing for the time being...
* '''King Arthur:''' Maybe later then?
* '''Player:''' Maybe so.
* {{tact|end}}

===Subsequent dialogue with King Arthur===
* '''King Arthur:''' How goes thy quest?
* '''Player:''' I am making progress, but I have not recovered the Grail yet.
* '''King Arthur:''' Well, the Grail IS very elusive, it may take some perseverance.
* '''King Arthur:''' As I said before, speak to Merlin in the workshop by the library.
* {{tact|end}}

==Talking to Merlin==
* '''Player:''' Hello. King Arthur has sent me on a quest for the Holy Grail. He thought you could offer some assistance.
* '''Merlin:''' Ah yes... the Holy Grail...
* '''Merlin:''' That is a powerful artefact indeed. Returning it here would help Camelot a lot.
* '''Merlin:''' Due to its nature the Holy Grail is likely to reside in a holy place.
* '''Player:''' Any suggestions?
* '''Merlin:''' I believe there is a holy island somewhere not far away... I'm not entirely sure... I spent too long inside that crystal! Anyway, go and talk to someone over there.
* '''Merlin:''' I suppose you could also try speaking to Sir Galahad?
* '''Merlin:''' He returned from the quest many years after everyone else. He seems to know something about it, but he can only speak about those experiences cryptically.
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Thank you for the advice.}}
** '''Player:''' Thank you for the advice.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Where can I find Sir Galahad?}}
** '''Player:''' Where can I find Sir Galahad?
** '''Merlin:''' Galahad now lives a life of religious contemplation. He lives somewhere west of McGrubor's Wood I think.
** {{tact|end}}

===Updating King Arthur===
* '''King Arthur:''' How goes thy quest?
* '''Player:''' I am making progress, but I have not recovered the Grail yet.
* '''King Arthur:''' Well, the Grail IS very elusive, it may take some perseverance.
* {{tact|end}}

==Asking the other Knights==

===Talking to Sir Palomedes===
* '''Sir Palomedes:''' Hello there adventurer, what do you want of me?
* '''Player:''' I'd like some advice on finding the Grail.
* '''Sir Palomedes:''' Sorry, I cannot help you with that.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Lucan===
* '''Sir Lucan:''' Hello there adventurer.
* '''Player:''' I seek the Grail of legend!
* '''Sir Lucan:''' I'm afraid I don't have any suggestions...
* '''Player:''' Thanks. I'll try and find someone who does.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Gawain===
* '''Sir Gawain:''' Good day to you!
* '''Player:''' I seek the Grail in the name of Camelot!
* '''Sir Gawain:''' The Grail? That is truly a noble quest indeed. None but Galahad have come close.
* '''Player:''' Galahad? Who is he?
* '''Sir Gawain:''' He used to be one of the Knights of the Round Table, but he mysteriously disappeared many years ago.
* '''Player:''' Why would he quit being a Knight?
* '''Sir Gawain:''' That is a good question.
* '''Sir Gawain:''' I'm afraid I don't have the answer.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Kay===
* '''Sir Kay:''' Good morrow!
* '''Sir Kay:''' I hear you are questing for the Holy Grail?!
* '''Player:''' That's right. Any hints?
* '''Sir Kay:''' Unfortunately not, Sirrah.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Tristam===
* '''Sir Tristram:''' Hail Arthur, King of the Britons!
* '''Player:''' Um... Hello.
* '''Player:''' I am seeking the Grail...
* '''Sir Tristram:''' Good luck with that!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Pellas===
* '''Sir Pelleas:''' Greetings to the court of King Arthur!
* '''Player:''' Any suggestions on finding the Grail?
* '''Sir Pelleas:''' My best guess would be some sort of spell. Merlin is our magic expert. Ask him?
* '''Sir Pelleas:''' Although having said that, I believe Galahad found its location once...
* '''Player:''' Really? Know where I can find him?
* '''Sir Pelleas:''' I'm afraid not. He left here many moons ago and I know not where he went.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Bedivere===
* '''Sir Bedivere:''' May I help you?
* '''Sir Bedivere:''' You are looking for the Grail now adventurer?
* '''Player:''' Absolutely.
* '''Sir Bedivere:''' The best of luck to you! Make the name of Camelot proud, and bring it back to us.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Sir Lancelot===
* '''Sir Lancelot:''' Greetings! I am Sir Lancelot, the greatest Knight in the land! What do you want?
* '''Player:''' I am questing for the Holy Grail.
* '''Sir Lancelot:''' The Grail? Ha! Frankly, friend, you're not in that league.
* '''Player:''' Why do you say that?
* '''Sir Lancelot:''' You got lucky with freeing Merlin but there's no way a puny wannabe like you is going to find the Holy Grail where so many others have failed.
* '''Player:''' We'll see about that.
* {{tact|end}}

==Talking to the High Priest of Entrana==
* '''High Priest:''' Many greetings. Welcome to our fair island.
* '''Player:''' Hello, I am in search of the Holy Grail.
* '''High Priest:''' The object of which you speak did once pass through holy Entrana. I know not where it is now however.
* '''High Priest:''' Nor do I really care.
* '''Crone:''' Did you say the Grail? You are a Grail knight, yes? Well you'd better hurry. A Fisher King is in pain.
* '''Player:''' Well I would, but I don't know where I am going!
* '''Crone:''' Go to where the six heads face, blow the whistle and away you go!
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|What are the six heads?}}
** '''Player:''' What are the six heads?
** '''Crone:''' The six stone heads have appeared just recently in the world. They all face the point of realm crossing. Find where two of the heads face,
** '''Crone:''' and you should be able to pinpoint where it is.
** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|What's a Fisher King?}}
** '''Player:''' What's a Fisher King?
** '''Crone:''' The Fisher King is the owner and slave of the Grail...
** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|Ok, I will go searching.}}
** '''Player:''' Ok, I will go searching.
** '''Crone:''' Good luck with that.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What do you mean by the whistle?}}
** '''Player:''' What do you mean by the whistle?
** '''Crone:''' You don't know about the whistles yet? The whistles are easy.
** '''Crone:''' You will need one to get to and from the Fisher King's realm. They reside in a haunted manor house in Misthalin, though you may not perceive them unless you carry something from the realm of the Fisher
** '''Crone:''' King...
** {{tselect|Select an option}}
** {{topt|What's a Fisher King?}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Ok, I will go searching.}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|What do you mean by the whistle?}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|The point of realm crossing?}}
*** '''Player:''' The point of realm crossing?
*** '''Crone:''' The realm of the Fisher King is not quite of this reality. It is of a reality very close to ours though... Where it is easiest to cross, THAT is a point of realm crossing.
*** {{tact|end}}

==Talking to Sir Galahad==
* '''Galahad:''' Welcome to my home. It's rare for me to have guests! Would you like a cup of tea? I'll just put the kettle on.
* {{tbox|Brother Galahad hangs a kettle over the fire.}}
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Are you any relation to Sir Galahad?}}
* {{topt|I'm on a quest to find the Holy Grail!}}
** '''Player:''' I'm on a quest to find the Holy Grail!
** '''Galahad:''' Ah... the Grail... yes... that did fill me with wonder! Oh, that I could have stayed forever! The spear, the food, the people...
** {{tselect|Select an option}}
** {{topt|So how can I find it?}}
** {{topt|What are you talking about?}}
*** '''Player:''' What are you talking about?
*** '''Galahad:''' The Grail castle... It's... hard to describe with words. It mostly felt like a dream!
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Why did you leave?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why did you leave?
*** '''Galahad:''' Apparently the time is getting close when the world will need Arthur and his knights of the round table again.
*** '''Galahad:''' And that includes me.
*** '''Galahad:''' Leaving was tough for me, so I took this small cloth from the table as a keepsake.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Why didn't you bring the Grail with you?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why didn't you bring the Grail with you?
*** '''Galahad:''' ...I'm not sure. Because... it seemed to be... NEEDED in the Grail castle? Half a moment, your cup of tea is ready.
*** {{tbox|Sir Galahad gives you a cup of tea.}}
*** {{tact|receives=a cup of tea}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|So how can I find it?}}
*** '''Player:''' So how can I find it?
*** '''Galahad:''' I did not find it through looking - though admittedly I looked long and hard - eventually, it found me.
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Well, I'd better be going then.}}
*** '''Player:''' Well, I'd better be going then.
*** '''Galahad:''' Half a moment, your cup of tea is ready.
*** {{tbox|Sir Galahad gives you a cup of tea.}}
*** {{tact|receives=a cup of tea}}
*** '''Galahad:''' If you do come across any particularily{{sic|Spelled particularly}} difficult obstacles on your quest, do not hesitate to ask my advice.
*** '''Galahad:''' I know more about the realm of the Grail than many, and I have a feeling you may need to come back and speak to me anyway...
* {{topt|quest=No|Do you get lonely here on your own?}}
* {{tcond|If the player talked to the High Priest of Entrana first:}}
** {{topt|I seek an item from the realm of the Fisher King.}}
*** '''Player:''' I seek an item from the realm of the Fisher King.
*** '''Galahad:''' Funny you should mention that, but when I left there I took this small cloth from the table as a keepsake.
*** '''Player:''' I don't suppose I could borrow that? It could come in useful on my quest.
*** {{tbox|Galahad reluctantly passes you a small cloth.}}
*** {{tact|receives=a Holy table napkin}}
*** {{tact|end}}

===Blowing on the [[Magic whistle]]===
* {{tcond|If the player blows the whistle anywhere besides between the four pillars at [[Brimhaven]]:}}
** {{tbox|The whistle makes no noise. It will not work in this location.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player blows the whistle whilst inside the [[Fisher Realm]]:}}
