* {{topt|Actually I think I'll run away!}}
** '''Player:''' Actually I think I'll run away!
** {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to talk to the Black Knight Titan again after his defeat===
* {{tact|above}}

==Talking to the Fisherman==
* '''Fisherman:''' Hi! I don't get many visitors here!
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|How's the fishing?}}
** '''Player:''' How's the fishing?
** '''Fisherman:''' Not amazing. Not many fish can live in this gungey stuff. I remember when this was a pleasant river teeming with every sort of fish...
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Any idea how to get into the castle?}}
** '''Player:''' Any idea how to get into the castle?
** '''Fisherman:''' Why, that's easy!
** '''Fisherman:''' Just ring one of the bells outside.
** '''Player:''' ...I didn't see any bells.
** '''Fisherman:''' You must be blind then. There's ALWAYS bells there when I go to the castle.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Yes, well, this place is a dump.}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, well, this place is a dump!
** '''Fisherman:''' This place used to be very beautiful, however, as our king grows old and weak, the land seems to be dying too.
** {{tact|end}}

===Peasant===
* '''Peasant:''' Woe is me! Our crops are all failing... how shall I feed myself this winter?
* {{tact|end}}

==Ringing the [[Grail bell]]==
* {{tcond|If the player rings the Grail bell but is not by the dismantled bricks:}}
** {{tbox|Ting-a-ling-a-ling!}}
** {{mes|Nothing happens.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player rings the Grail bell and is at least four tiles by the dismantled bricks:}}
** {{tbox|Ting-a-ling-a-ling!}}
** '''Grail Maiden:''' Welcome to the Grail castle. You should come inside, it's cold out here.
** {{tbox|Somehow you are now inside the castle.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to a Grail Maiden===
* '''Grail Maiden:''' Welcome to the Grail castle.
* {{tact|end}}

===Taking the [[Holy grail (item)|holy grail]] before talking to the Fisher King===
* {{tbox|You feel that the Grail shouldn't be moved. You must complete some task here before you are worthy.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Talking to [[The Fisher King]]==
* '''The Fisher King:''' Ah! You got inside at last! You spent all that time fumbling around outside, I thought you'd never make it here.
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|How did you know what I have been doing?}}
** '''Player:''' How did you know what I have been doing?
** '''The Fisher King:''' Oh, I can see what is happening in my realm. I have sent clues to help you get here, such as the fisherman, and the crone.
** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|I seek the Holy Grail.}}
** '''Player:''' I seek the Holy Grail.
** '''The Fisher King:''' Ah excellent. A knight come to seek the Holy Grail. Maybe our land can be restored to its former glory.
** '''The Fisher King:''' At the moment the Grail cannot be removed from the castle. Legend has it a questing knight will one day work out how to restore our land; then he will claim the Grail as his prize.
** '''Player:''' Any ideas how I can restore the land?
** '''The Fisher King:''' None at all.
** {{tselect|Select an option}}
** {{topt|You don't look too well.}}
*** '''Player:''' You don't look too well.
*** '''The Fisher King:''' Nope, I don't feel so good either.
*** '''The Fisher King:''' I fear my life is running short... Alas, my son and heir is not here. I am waiting for my son to return to this castle.
*** '''The Fisher King:''' If you could find my son, that would be a great weight off my shoulders.
*** '''Player:''' Who is your son?
*** '''The Fisher King:''' He is known as Percival.
*** '''The Fisher King:''' I believe he is a knight of the round table.
*** '''Player:''' I shall go and see if I can find him.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Do you mind if I have a look around?}}
*** '''Player:''' Do you mind if I have a look around?
*** '''The Fisher King:''' No, not at all. Please, be my guest.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|You don't look too well.}}
** {{tact|above}}

==Talking to King Arthur==
* '''Player:''' Hello, do you have a knight named Sir Percival?
* '''King Arthur:''' Ah yes. I remember young Percival. He rode off on a quest a couple of months ago. We are getting a bit worried, he's not back yet...
* '''King Arthur:''' He was going to try and recover the golden boots of Arkaneeses.
* '''Player:''' Any idea which way that would be?
* '''King Arthur:''' Not exactly. We discovered some magic golden feathers that are said to point the way to the boots...
* '''King Arthur:''' They certainly point somewhere.
* '''King Arthur:''' Just blowing gently on them will supposedly show the way to go.
* {{tcond|If the player does not have enough inventory space:}}
** '''King Arthur:''' Free up some space and I'll give you a feather.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has one free inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Magic gold feather detail.png|King Arthur gives you a feather.}}
** {{tact|receives=a Magic gold feather}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player loses the feather:}}
** {{tact|initial}}

