==Talking to Sir Percival==
* {{tcond|If the player prods at the sacks:}}
** {{tbox|You hear a muffled groan. The sack wriggles slightly.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player attempts to open the sack:}}
** {{tbox|You hear muffled noises from the sack. You open the sack.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Sir Percival:''' Wow, thank you! I could hardly breathe in there!
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|How did you end up in a sack?}}
** '''Player:''' How did you end up in a sack?
** '''Sir Percival:''' It's a little embarrassing really.
** '''Sir Percival:''' After going on a long and challenging quest to retrieve the boots of Arkaneeses, defeating many powerful enemies on the way, I fell into a goblin trap!
** '''Sir Percival:''' I've been kept as a slave here for the last 3 months!
** '''Sir Percival:''' A day or so ago, they decided it was a fun game to put me in this sack:{{sic|Supposed to be a semicolon}} then they forgot about me!
** '''Sir Percival:''' I'm now very hungry, and my bones feel very stiff.
** {{tact|inital}}
* {{topt|Come with me, I shall make you a king.}}
** '''Player:''' Come with me, I shall make you a king.
** '''Sir Percival:''' What are you talking about?
** '''Sir Percival:''' The king of where?
** '''Player:''' Your father is apparently someone called the Fisher King. He is dying and wishes you to be his heir.
** '''Sir Percival:''' I have been told that before.
** '''Sir Percival:''' I have not been able to find that castle again though...
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the whistle:}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I do have the means to get us there - wait, let me go get the magic whistle!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the magic whistle:}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I do have the means to get us there - a magic whistle!
** {{tbox|You give a whistle to Sir Percival. You tell sir Percival what to do with the whistle.}}
** '''Sir Percival:''' Ok, I will see you there then!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Your father wishes to speak to you.}}
** '''Player:''' Your father wishes to speak to you.
** '''Sir Percival:''' My father? You have spoken to him recently?
** '''Player:''' He is dying and wishes you to be his heir.
** '''Sir Percival:''' I have been told that before.
** '''Sir Percival:''' I have not been able to find that castle again though...
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the whistle:}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I do have the means to get us there - wait, let me go get the magic whistle!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the magic whistle:}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I do have the means to get us there - a magic whistle!
** {{tbox|You give a whistle to Sir Percival. You tell sir Percival what to do with the whistle.}}
** '''Sir Percival:''' Ok, I will see you there then!
** {{tact|end}}

===Subsequent dialogue with Sir Percival===
* '''Sir Percival:''' I said I will see you there then!
* {{tact|end}}

